**Average Accounts Receivable**

\[
\frac{\text{Accounts Receivable (2024)} + \text{Accounts Receivable (2023)}}{2}
= \frac{1{,}213.8\;+\;1{,}184.1}{2}
= \frac{2{,}397.9}{2}
= 1{,}198.95
\]

**Result:** **≈ $1,199 million** (average accounts receivable).

**Days Sales Outstanding (DSO)**  

\[
\text{DSO}= \frac{\text{Average Accounts Receivable} \times 365}{\text{Revenue}}
\]

- Average Accounts Receivable  
  \[
  \frac{1{,}213.8 + 1{,}184.1}{2}=1{,}198.95\ \text{(million)}
  \]

- Revenue (total net revenues for FY 2024)  
  \[
  36{,}176.2\ \text{(million)}
  \]

\[
\text{DSO}= \frac{1{,}198.95 \times 365}{36{,}176.2}
          = \frac{437{,}616.75}{36{,}176.2}
          \approx 12.1\ \text{days}
\]

**Answer:** **≈ 12.1 days**.

**Average Accounts Payable**

\[
\frac{\text{Accounts Payable (2024)} + \text{Accounts Payable (2023)}}{2}
= \frac{1{,}595.5\ \text{(million)} + 1{,}544.3\ \text{(million)}}{2}
= \frac{3{,}139.8}{2}
= 1{,}569.9\ \text{million}
\]

**Result:** **$1,569.9 million**.

**Average Net Fixed Assets**

\[
\frac{\text{Net Fixed Assets (2024)} + \text{Net Fixed Assets (2023)}}{2}
= \frac{8{,}665.5\ \text{million} + 7{,}387.1\ \text{million}}{2}
= \frac{16{,}052.6\ \text{million}}{2}
= 8{,}026.3\ \text{million}
\]

**Result:** **$8,026.3 million**.

**Average Total Assets**

\[
\frac{\text{Total Assets (2024)} + \text{Total Assets (2023)}}{2}
= \frac{31{,}339.3 + 29{,}445.5}{2}
= \frac{60{,}784.8}{2}
= 30{,}392.4
\]

**Result:** **30,392.4** (in the same monetary units as the tables, i.e., $ millions).
